      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_14_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_14",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six powerplant. This high-revving mill utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band and an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory M-variable differential lock. The chassis is well-sorted, benefiting from documented subframe reinforcement and a refreshed suspension featuring Bilstein dampers. Recent preventative maintenance includes a valve clearance adjustment and a cooling system overhaul with a metal-impeller water pump. While the exterior shows minor stone chips and light patina consistent with a well-loved driver's car, the mechanical integrity remains robust. This M3 offers the communicative hydraulic steering rack and neutral handling balance that defined an era of performance engineering.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
